{"word":"θαυμαστέος","slug":"θαυμαστέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>θαυμαστέος</b></el> <el>(θαυμαστέος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:θαυμάζω'><el>θαυμάζω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be admired</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <el>θαυμαστέον</el>, <i>one must admire</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}